===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|ojp|ja}} root verb {{m|ja|す|tr=su||to do}}.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref><ref name="DJR">{{R:Daijirin}}</ref>

As with all verbs, during the Middle Japanese stage in the [[w:Kamakura period|Kamakura]] and [[w:Muromachi period|Muromachi]] periods, the {{m|ja|終止形|tr=shūshikei||terminal or sentence-ending form}} was gradually lost as the {{m|ja|連体形|tr=rentaikei||attributive form}} came to be used for both the attributive and terminal grammatical roles, realigning the conjugations.

